Q: Given the array below, use loop to remove and print each name. 
   Stop the loop once names doesn't contain any more elements.

   names = ['Sally', 'Joe', 'Lisa', 'Henry']

   My A:

   loop do
     name = names.shift
     puts name
     break if names.size == 0
   end

   LS A:

   names = ['Sally', 'Joe', 'Lisa', 'Henry']

  loop do
    puts names.shift
    break if names.empty?
  end

